Botswana celebrated its 50th independence anniversary on Saturday with cultural activities at the Louis Leaky Auditorium Nairobi.The event was hosted by Botswana High Commissioner to Kenya John Moreti. Tswana dancers entertained the Batswana and invited guests. Guests also got an opportunity to taste some Botswana delicacies.The Tswana dancers have performed across the world. Earlier, the Botswana High Commission and Know Your World Initiative, which educates students on international affairs, organised a forum to create awareness about Botswana.